"n. 极光(南北极夜晚所放彩光) 【同】 派生词: auroral adj.极光的 n. 极光(南北极夜晚所放出的彩光) 【源】源于罗马神话中的奥罗拉黎明女神, 据说极光预示着黎明的到来. 【记】发音酷似""quot;""quot;好柔弱""quot;""quot;－当然柔弱了, 这可是北极的美眉, 你在这能看见就不错了! 【记】Au 化学元素金 + 音：柔弱→柔弱的金光→极光 aurora (n.)  late 14c., from Latin Aurora, the Roman goddess of dawn, from PIE *ausus- ""dawn,"" also the name of the Indo-European goddess of the dawn, from root *aus- (1) ""to shine,"" especially of the dawn (cognates: Greek eos ""dawn,"" auein ""to dry, kindle;"" Sanskrit usah, Lithuanian ausra ""dawn;"" Latin auster ""south wind,"" usum ""to burn;"" Old English east ""east"")."
